casebody.data:
McSorley v. Faulkner. (Common Pleas of New York City and County,

General Term.

May 12, 1892.) Action by Alexander McSorley against James A. Faulkner.

Argued before Bookstaver and Bischoff, JJ.

Ho opinion. Motion for- reargument or leave to appeal to the court of appeals denied, with $10 costs. See 14 N. Y. Supp. 789; 18 N. Y. Supp. 461.
